Subject: Συναυλίες, Όπερα, Συμφωνική, Μουσεία, άλλα events
Description:
1.	Cultural Enrichment:
	*	Set a reminder to book a guided tour of a local art gallery or museum.
	*	Schedule an evening to attend a poetry reading or a play at a community theater.
2.	Reconnecting:
	*	Plan a weekend to visit a hometown or a place with sentimental value.
	*	Arrange a catch-up call or a reunion with an old friend or a group of friends from your past.
3.	Outdoor Adventures:
	*	Organize a day trip to a national park or a botanical garden.
	*	Book a lesson or a guided experience for outdoor activities like kayaking, rock climbing, or mountain biking.
4.	Creative Outlets:
	*	Enroll in a workshop or a class for something you've never tried before, like pottery, painting, or dance.
	*	Set aside time to start writing a blog, a story, or even begin a video vlog.
5.	Culinary Experiences:
	*	Plan to attend a food festival or a street food market to try new cuisines.
	*	Schedule a cooking class to learn how to prepare a dish from a different culture.
6.	Personal Challenges:
	*	Book a tandem skydiving jump or a flying lesson to overcome fears and enjoy the thrill.
	*	Commit to a "DIY Day" where you build or create something from scratch—like homebrewing beer or assembling a piece of furniture.
7.	Health and Wellness:
	*	Sign up for a yoga retreat or a meditation workshop to improve mental and physical well-being.
	*	Arrange regular hiking or cycling weekends to explore new trails while keeping fit.
8.	Entertainment and Arts:
	*	Reserve tickets for an upcoming opera, ballet, or symphony orchestra performance.
	*	Look for a local jazz club or an open-mic night and schedule a visit.
9.	Learning and Development:
	*	Register for a language learning class or a cultural exchange meetup.
	*	Find a lecture or a seminar on a topic you're curious about, like astronomy or history, and book your spot.
10.	Adventure and Sport:
*         Plan a horseback riding session in the countryside.
*         Look into scuba diving certifications or surf lessons if you're near the coast.

Subject: MSCA RISE NeuronsXnets Analysis Workshop 2024
Description:
The NeuronsXnets Analysis Workshop 2024, scheduled for July 1-2 at the Foundation for Research and Technology-Hellas, will bring together leading researchers to discuss advancements in neuroscience and artificial intelligence. The workshop will kick off on  July 1 with a welcome and introduction to the MSCA NeuronsXnets Project, followed by in-depth presentations from prominent scientists. Highlights include Peyman Golshani's exploration of working memory representations, Stelios Smirnakis's insights from a mouse  model of bistable perception, and Gabriel Kreiman's comparison of AI vision systems to biological visual processing. The second day will feature discussions on functional connectivity in the brain by Maria Papadopouli, Ioannis Smyrnakis's study of neuronal  activity transmission, and Angeliki Pantazi's presentation on neuro-inspired computing. The event will conclude with a session on challenges in machine learning for big scientific data analysis led by Greg Tsagkatakis and a panel discussion on Neurocentric  AI.

You can register at: https://forms.gle/jxbXy5TQ7Kbsvj699 <https://emea01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fforms.gle%2FjxbXy5TQ7Kbsvj699&data=05%7C02%7C%7C306ff15090e141e1754e08dc7f125fe6%7C84df9e7fe9f640afb435aaaaaaaaaaaa%7C1%7C0%7C638524964097547653%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&sdata=TSAMywGOITm%2BNaWqmhiZOtUTI%2BsGiixHDd%2FnEDi6JqI%3D&reserved=0>
